[{"id":"VH962538","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"A block with a mass of m is shown at the top of an inclined plane. The inclined plane forms an angle of theta with the horizontal. The coefficient of kinetic friction between the surface of the inclined plane and the block is labeled mu.\" height=\"120\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH962538.g01.png\" width=\"450\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A block of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m\"><math alttext=\"m\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is sliding down an inclined plane that makes an angle <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta\"><math alttext=\"theta\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> with the horizontal, as shown in the figure. The coefficient of kinetic friction between the surface and the block is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"mu\"><math alttext=\"mu\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>μ</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> . Which of the following is a correct expression for the acceleration <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"a\"><math alttext=\"a\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>a</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> of the block?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH962538_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"g times, open parenthesis, 1 minus mu cosine theta, close parenthesis\"><math alttext=\"g times, open parenthesis, 1 minus mu cosine theta, close parenthesis\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>−</mo><mi>μ</mi><mi>cos</mi><mi>θ</mi></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><spa